Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I go to Page 06 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Corpus uteri mass' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is preselected
And 'I describe' button is preselected

When I select 'Differential diagnosis' tab
Then 'Differential diagnosis 1*' dropdown is enabled

When I select 'Leiomyoma' from 'Differential diagnosis 1*' dropdown
Then 'FIGO Classification' localizer is displayed
And 'Degeneration' dropdown is displayed
And 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown is enabled

When I open 'FIGO Classification' localizer and select any part
Then the part is selected and diplayed

When I open 'Degeneration' dropdown and select any option
Then the option is selected and displayed

When I select 'Endometrial carcinoma' from 'Differential diagnosis 1*' dropdown
Then 'Stage I: Limited to corpus uteri' radio button is displayed
And 'Stage II: Cervical infiltration' radio button is displayed
And 'Stage III: Local and/or regional spread' radio button is displayed
And 'Stage IV: Advanced tumor stage' radio button is displayed

When I select 'Stage I: Limited to corpus uteri' radio button
Then 'Details stage I*' dropdown is enabled

When I open 'Details stage I*' dropdown and click any option
Then an option is selected

When I select 'Stage III: Local and/or regional spread' radio button
Then 'Details stage III*' dropdown is enabled

When I open 'Details stage III*' dropdown and click  option 'IIIC: Metastases in pelvic and/or paraaortic lymph nodes (up to renal vessels)
Then 'Additional information*' dropdown is enabled

When I open 'Additional information*' dropdown and click any option
Then an option is selected

When I select 'Stage IV: Advanced tumor stage' radio button
Then 'Details stage IV*' dropdown is enabled

When I open 'Details stage IV*' dropdown and click any option
Then an option is selected



When I am at the 'Characterization I' tab
And select any option from 'Differential diagnosis 1*' dropdown

And I select 'Differential diagnosis' tab
And I select 'Leiomyoma' from 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown
Then 'FIGO Classification' localizer is displayed
And 'Degeneration' dropdown is displayed
And 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled

When I open 'FIGO Classification' localizer and select any part
Then the part is selected and diplayed

When I open 'Degeneration' dropdown and click any option
Then the option is selected

When I select 'Endometrial carcinoma' from 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown
Then 'Stage I: Limited to corpus uteri' radio button is displayed
And 'Stage II: Cervical infiltration' radio button is displayed
And 'Stage III: Local and/or regional spread' radio button is displayed
And 'Stage IV: Advanced tumor stage' radio button is displayed

When I select 'Stage I: Limited to corpus uteri' radio button
Then 'Details stage I*' dropdown is enabled

When I open 'Details stage I*' dropdown and click any option
Then an option is selected

When I select 'Stage III: Local and/or regional spread' radio button
Then 'Details stage III*' dropdown is enabled

When I open 'Details stage III*' dropdown and click  option 'IIIC: Metastases in pelvic and/or paraaortic lymph nodes (up to renal vessels)
Then 'Additional information*' dropdown is enabled

When I open 'Additional information*' dropdown and click any option
Then an option is selected

When I select 'Stage IV: Advanced tumor stage' radio button
Then 'Details stage IV*' dropdown is enabled

When I open 'Details stage IV*' dropdown and click any option
Then an option is selected
